  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7001 sitting directly on the max positive gamma wall at 7000 (21.3B), dealers are actively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma concentration between 7000-7100 suggests dealers will aggressively fade any further upside momentum while providing support on dips back toward the 6860 flip level. The \"wall_break\" event confirms dealers are now defending this critical 7000 strike, with the next major resistance walls stacked at 7025 and 7050.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect strong selling pressure to cap gains near current levels with downside support around 6860.",
